Full SHA-256 of "abc" in Verbose, parameterized on which 32-bit word
to extract (0..7). Running the binary 8 times with argv 0..7 yields
all 256 bits, matching `echo -n abc | sha256sum` byte-for-byte.
sha256_word(0)=0xba7816bf, sha256_word(1)=0x8f01cfea, etc.
End-to-end demonstration of crypto in Verbose.
